<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-288-239  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 288 239.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Jan 19 1989 v34 n2 p91(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Improvements make precision amps easier: manufacturers are makingquieter chopper-stabilized op amps that are also easier to use.andO;(includes related article on thermal design) (operationalamplifiers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Quinnell, Richard A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Chopper-stabilized op amps have experienced improvements recentlythat have made the op amps quieter and easier to use.andO;Chopper-stabilized op amps offer low offset-voltage drift--afeature that is used in applications such as strain-gaugeamplifiers, thermocouple amplifiers and precision data collectionin environments where periodic adjustments are difficult orimpossible.andP;  Manufacturers who want the best actual performancefrom op amps need to pay close attention to the thermocoupleeffect, which is formed when any dissimilar metals are connected.andO;The thermocouple effect produces an electric force that varieswith temperature.andP;  For good thermal design manufacturers shouldkeep heat sources several inches away from an amplifier circuitand avoid air flow over the amplifier area.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Operational amplifiersElectronic IndustryProduct DevelopmentVoltageCircuitryComputer Manufacture.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Correction of mulling amplifier. (chart)Clamping circuit for chopper-stabilized op amps. (chart)Built-in hold capacitors. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>